Joseph Koetters, a former English teacher at the Hancock Park school in Los Angeles, is being sued by an unnamed 30-year-old former student .
The lawsuit alleges that when he was in his early-to-mid 30s he took part in a yearlong sexual relationship with a 16-year old student, which began in the 2000-2001 school year .
Koetters pleaded not guilty and could face up to five years in prison if convicted .